Israel Chemicals, Bank Hapoalim, Leumi: Israeli Equity Preview

-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 
2011-10-04T07:24:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/israel-chemicals-bank-hapoalim-leumi-israeli-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in Israeli markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
company names and prices are from the last close unless
otherwise stated.  The TA-25 Index gained 0.7 percent to 1,061.08 in  Tel Aviv .  Bank Leumi Le- Israel  Ltd. (LUMI IT), Bank Hapoalim Ltd.
(POLI IT): The Bank of Israel will increase the core Tier-1
capital adequacy ratio target for the country’s banks to 11
percent by 2016 from the current 7.5 percent, Globes reported,
citing people it didn’t identify. A Bank of Israel spokesman
told Bloomberg News he is familiar with the subject but declined
to confirm specific facts, numbers or dates. Leumi, the
country’s largest bank by assets, declined 0.4 percent to 11.38
shekels. Hapoalim, Israel’s second-biggest bank by assets,
gained 0.6 percent to 13.12 shekels.  Israel Chemicals Ltd. (ICL)  : ICL Performance Products,
the company’s U.S. unit, acquired Halox, a division of Hammond
Group Inc. The shares of ICL, which extracts minerals from the
 Dead Sea  to make fertilizer and potash, declined 1.5 percent to
41.30 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
